	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=41108"><span id="Scholar">Azuarc</span></a><br /><b><span id="Scholar">Scholar</span></b><br /><span id="notbold">2317 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.02]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>&gt;&nbsp;&nbsp;Most 60 clerics are close or damn near maxed wis they dont NEED the wis. AC? bah clerics can wear plate i dont wanna hear it.<br/><br/>I'm one of those 60 clerics, and I'd take this item for the other stats and the chance to consolidate my wisdom.<br/>And the fact that I can wear plate excludes me from being allowed to have something you can use too? If you want to make that argument, then give it to a druid, you CHAIN-wearing fool.<br/><br/>While I doubt this is a paly item, it very well, could be, and I shudder to even tackle your comments on the paladin class. Let me just say they're outright wrong and not back it up. (Yes, I know I'm leaving myself open to flame.)<br/><br/>Druids in my guild rarely nuke on raids, seeing as they're the second best healers in the game. And if you have full Skyshrine minus vindi BP, you have much better gear, cross-class compared, than a druid wearing full elysium armor, which is inferior to their ToV armor, which is still partially inferior to your ToV armor since you wear chain. And idiots like you are the reason why the druids out there that would prefer to group are forced/compelled to solo sometimes.<br/><br/>No, not a ranger or a beastlord - they'd never want it - but any shield-using class listed is a viable option.<br/><br/><br/><br/>ok, now to comment on your follow-up post to the druid who posted telling you how correctly stupid you are...<br/><br/>Saying that slow makes or breaks &quot;some&quot; fights hardly says you know what you're talking about even within the bounds of your own class. And you clearly demonstrate that you haven't a clue what paladins or the &quot;spoiled&quot; druid class do.<br/>Let's start with this: druids are not spoiled. Clerics are spoiled. Shamans come next among priest classes. Look at the loots druids can use compared to you and you'll probably snicker at them for a moment and say it serves them right. Then consider that while druids have impressive soloing capabilities, so do shamans. I'd go so far as to say better. And try getting a group as a druid - or are they always expected to solo, shunned by the rest of the world except when your sorry self needs a port? If all you see if critical blasts from druids, ask them what else they do on raids - who they heal, what buffs they cast, how they help people get to and from the raids. Truth is druids and wizards do more work for a raid than most classes because they start earlier and end later. What do you do? Buff, cann a little, then slow. (Which is still more than I do, granted.)<br/>Paladins don't ever sit back and heal on raids. Their only two heals that really use are LoH and healing wave of prexus. LoH is usually used as a buffer initially to get a complete heal chain started, if not an emergency back-up system. Meantime that paly is fighting with the rest of the melees and occasionally repairing AE damage. If he takes aggro from LoH at the onset, which is likely, he'll probably die, and he'll suck it up because it's part of his job to keep the MT alive until you get your slow off.<br/>I could lecture some more np, but the rest of the people reading these boards don't need to read the posts buffoons like you make, or the idiots (me) who flame them back.<br/><br/>&gt;However I dont care about opinions as everyone knows the old saying.  Oh and by the way, you seem to have decided to talk down to me for my lack of knowledge.  I never claimed to be the best player or most well informed, however you're post means nothing to me.<br/>You sure seem to be full of it though...knowledge and opinions I mean.</p>&nbsp;<br /><span class=sm>-------